Bafana Bafana coach Hugo Broos. AFP/Yuri Cortez JOHANNESBURG - The new Bafana Bafana coach Hugo Broos arrived in the country on Monday, with no assistant to begin his tenure. Broos, who signed a five-year contract, was met by Safa President Danny Jordaan. READ: Broos signs five-year contract with SA The 62-year-old, a big believer in youth, is said to make big changes by dismantling the current team and putting together a team that stands a chance to qualify for the 2022 Fifa World Cup in Qatar. He will have ample time to prepare his side for the qualifier, which has now been moved to September against neighbours Zimbabwe.